item.title: TED: '3 lessons on success from an Arab businesswoman | Leila Hoteit'
item.description:
Professional Arab women juggle more responsibilities than their male counterparts, and they face more cultural rigidity than Western women. What can their success teach us about tenacity, competition, priorities and progress? Tracing her career as an engineer, advocate and mother in Abu Dhabi, Leila Hoteit shares three lessons for thriving in the modern world.

item.title: TED: 'When we design for disability, we all benefit | Elise Roy'
item.description:
"I believe that losing my hearing was one of the greatest gifts I've ever received," says Elise Roy. As a disability rights lawyer and design thinker, she knows that being Deaf gives her a unique way of experiencing and reframing the world -- a perspective that could solve some of our largest problems. As she says: "When we design for disability first, you often stumble upon solutions that are better than those when we design for the norm."

item.title: Genius: 'Desiigner - Tiimmy Turner (Official Timmy Turner Lyrics)'
item.description:
Desiigner - Tiimmy Turner (Official Genius lyric video)

These lyrics were all verified by Desiigner.

Desiigner’s latest single, “Tiimmy Turner,” went from an a cappella freestyle to a Top 40 hit. But just like his previous smash record “Panda,” there’s still plenty of confusion about what he’s saying in the song.

“I care about my lyrics. I have my own way of saying things—I call it new English,” Desiigner says. “When it came time to do the ‘Tiimmy Turner’ lyric video, I knew Genius would help me bring the words to life.”

Desiigner changed the song’s title from “Timmy Turner” to “Tiimmy Turner” to match the additional “i” in his own name.

Read more at: http://genius.com/a/desiigner-tiimmy-turner-the-official-lyric-video

Credits:

Directed and produced by Genius

Lyric animation by Violet Office

Computational art by Albert Omoss

item.title: Genius: 'Check the Rhyme: Kendrick Lamar on "THat Part (Black Hippy Remix)"'
item.description:
Minutes before the official release of his Blank Face album, ScHoolboy Q dropped the Black Hippy remix of his song “THat Part” On the Cardo, Cubeatz, Kanye West and Yung Exclusive-produced track, Kanye West’s verse is swapped out for features from Kendrick Lamar, Jay Rock, and Ab-Soul.

And, of course, Kendrick’s verse has everyone talking. Kendrick employs multiple rhyme schemes and internal rhymes on each of the 24 bars.
